------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[G] Verdict
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Windows VM windows@192.168.65.8 is severely memory-starved as of the test window.
Even bare 'hostname' over SSH crashes the login shell on assembly load
("paging file is too small"). PowerShell module autoload triggers
System.OutOfMemoryException. cmd.exe /c <anything heavy> returns the same.

The Phase 23 reviewer's working pattern ('cmd.exe /c powershell.exe
-EncodedCommand <b64>') was observed historically; the VM has degraded
further since that observation - this validation cannot get even bare
SSH to stay alive long enough to scp the orchestrator wrapper.

This is operator/user territory per the Phase 25 prompt:
   "Do NOT spend more than 30 minutes troubleshooting VM-level issues -
    that's operator/user territory."

Remediation required (operator): increase the Windows guest paging file
size and/or RAM allocation in the UTM VM definition for windows-utm-1,
restart the guest, and re-run Phase 25 validation.

Of note for the operator: the existing RustyNet install on the VM
appears to be from a prior bootstrap. Phase 25 validation against that
prior install cannot be completed in the current degraded state - both
"observe Windows daemon state" (Step 4) and "verify named-pipe ACL"
(Step 5) require running PowerShell / rustynetd.exe successfully, and
neither is currently possible.
